### How are you embracing sustainability throughout your product design and delivery?

At Wype, sustainability is more than just an initiative—it’s core to our mission. From product design to delivery, we strive to minimize environmental impact while prioritizing quality. Our toilet paper is crafted from organic bamboo, a renewable resource that regenerates rapidly. It’s also unwhitened and unbleached, eliminating the need for harmful chemicals like bleach, formaldehyde, PFAS, and BPA, ensuring both skin safety and ecological responsibility.

Our manufacturing partner, [LC Paper](https://www.lcpaper.com/), shares our sustainability values and leads by example. With over 140 years of experience, LC Paper was the first B Corp-certified paper manufacturer globally, underscoring its commitment to creating zero-impact products. Their factory utilizes renewable energy from 8,500 solar panels, powering one of the region's largest solar farms. Additionally, they employ biomass and biomethane energy to ensure thermal energy production remains sustainable. No plastic is used in packaging, and shipments rely on electrified trains whenever possible to minimize carbon emissions.

This partnership allows Wype to deliver eco-conscious products that are traceable, biodegradable, and fully aligned with our vision for a cleaner, greener future. By integrating circular processes and renewable energy into every step, Wype offers a truly sustainable solution for modern hygiene.

### Where do you source your materials from?

Our bamboo is responsibly harvested from regions in Asia where farming practices prioritize sustainability and environmental conservation. After harvested, the raw bamboo pulp is transported to our manufacturing partner, where they are processed into high-quality, eco-friendly Facial Tissues and Toilet Paper rolls for our community.

We work exclusively with trusted suppliers who share our values of ethical cultivation and sustainable practices, ensuring minimal impact on surrounding ecosystems. Bamboo, as a renewable resource, grows rapidly and regenerates naturally, making it an ideal alternative to trees for paper production. By sourcing and processing responsibly, we actively help reduce deforestation and preserve biodiversity while supporting a cleaner, greener planet.


### What markets do you serve currently?

Currently, Wype serves environmentally conscious customers across Canada and the USA. Our focus is on supporting individuals and businesses who prioritize a lifestyle change and are committed to creating a positive impact for the environment. We provide sustainable, high-quality products made without using harsh unnecessary chemicals to ultra-process and whiten tissue paper, ensuring a gentler solution for both people and the planet.



### Why did you choose a .eco domain for your business?

The .eco domain perfectly reflects who we are and what we stand for. It is a direct representation of our commitment to sustainability, environmental responsibility, and eco-friendly practices. Having a .eco domain makes it clear to our customers and partners that our values are rooted in making a positive impact on the planet. It also helps us align with like-minded communities that care deeply about environmental issues and inspires trust among our environmentally conscious audience.


